properties.name: name
properties.description: Name of custom variable

properties.name: value
properties.description: Value of custom variable

properties.name: isMobile
properties.description: Weather current running environment is mobile device.

properties.name: updateCustomVariable
properties.description: Update custom variable.

properties.name: type
properties.description:
Type of button, possible options are:
+ 'monitor' - monitor button
+ 'text' - text button
+ 'static' - static image button
+ 'float' - float image button
+ 'mobile-image' - mobile image button
+ 'mobile-text' - mobile text button
+ 'adaptive' - adaptive button

properties.name: campaignId
properties.description: Campaign id of button

properties.name: click
properties.description:
Simulate click behavior, the same as user click on this chat
button.

properties.name: onStatusChange
properties.description:
Register callback,
which will be notified when status of current campaign changed.

properties.name: id
properties.description: Uniq of agent

properties.name: name
properties.description: Display name of agent

properties.name: avatar
properties.description: Source of avatar image

properties.name: bio
properties.description: Bio description of agent

properties.name: title
properties.description: Title of agent

properties.name: type
properties.description:
Type of invitation, possible options are:
+ 'image' - image invitation
+ 'adaptive' - adaptive invitation
+ 'embedded-window' - popup embedded chat window directly
+ 'mobile' - mobile invitation

properties.name: message
properties.description: Message of current invitation.

properties.name: agent
properties.description: Agent info, will only be provided if it's a manual invitation.

properties.name: accept
properties.description: Accept invitation manually

properties.name: refuse
properties.description: Refuse invitation manually

properties.name: onAccept
properties.description:
Register callback function when invitation is
accepted (either by visitor or programatically).

properties.name: onRefuse
properties.description:
Register callback function when invitation is
refused.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Type of message

properties.name: sender
properties.description:
Sender of message, possible types of sender are:
+ 'visitor'
+ 'agent'
+ 'system'

properties.name: time
properties.description: Creating time of this message

properties.name: content
properties.description: Detailed content of message

params.name: index
params.description: Index of current message (in messasge list)

return.description:
The transformed message. If `null` is provided, this
message will be removed from list; if a list of message is provided, all of them will be rendered
in list.

properties.name: onChange
properties.description:
Register callback function to
transform message in list.  possible message types are:
+ 'waiting-queue'
+ 'agent-join'
+ 'agent-leave'
+ 'agent-text'
+ 'visitor-text'
+ 'end-chat'
+ ...

properties.name: type
properties.description:
Type of field, possible types are:
+ 'input' - single line input field
+ 'textarea' - Multiple line input field
+ 'radiolist' - Group of radio buttons
+ 'checkbox' - Single checkbox field
+ 'select' - Dropdown list field
+ 'checkboxlist' - Group of checkbox
+ 'file' - Attachment upload field
+ 'email' - Input field that accept email address
+ 'ticket' - Input field that accept Comm100 Ticket number
+ 'department' - Dropdown list that display available department
+ 'stars' - Field for user to rate the chat (select from 1 to 5 stars by default)
+ 'custom' - Custom field that display whatever user provide in element property

properties.name: name
properties.description: Label name of field

properties.name: value
properties.description: Value of current field

properties.name: isSystem
properties.description: Whether the field is system field

properties.name: error
properties.description:
Potential error of this field with current value. This error might
or might not be displayed, usually it will be displayed after field blur or before form submit.

properties.name: options
properties.description:
Possible options of current field, only
valid when type is `select`, `radiobox` or `checkbox`.

properties.name: element
properties.description: Extended element, only valid when type is `custom`

params.name: prevFields
params.description:
Previous version of fields. For initial run, this will be
default value.

return.description: form data that should be submitted.

properties.name: onChange
properties.description:
Transform original fields to match
situation.

properties.name: onSubmit
properties.description:
Transform original submit
data, use this API if you would like to provide field data programatically.

properties.name: onError
properties.description:
Trigger callback when error
occurs. For example, when providing incorrect submit data.

properties.name: submit
properties.description: Submit form with provided data.

properties.name: render
properties.description: Render form directly

return.description:
If provides an HTMLElement, original component will not be rendered;
if provides null, use original component instead.

If `null` is provided, this tab will be hide temporarily; otherwise,
HTMLElement will be append to this tab.

properties.name: attachTab
properties.description: Extends extra window with one more tab.

properties.name: show
properties.description:
Display specific
extended tab, rendering the tab with given parameters. If none `tab` is provided, it will
display default tab if there is any.

properties.name: hide
properties.description: Hide extra extended window.

properties.name: campaignId
properties.description: Campaign id

properties.name: minimize
properties.description: Minimize current chat window

properties.name: onMinimize
properties.description:
Register callback which will be
called when chat window is minimized.

properties.name: close
properties.description: Close current chat window

properties.name: onClose
properties.description:
Register callback which will
be called when chat window is closed

properties.name: endChat
properties.description: End current chat

properties.name: onEndChat
properties.description:
Register callback which will
be called when chat is ended

properties.name: restore
properties.description: Restore current chat window

properties.name: onRestore
properties.description:
Register callback which will
be called when chat window is restored

properties.name: onRender
properties.description:
Render customized element. If callback provies an HTMLElement, original component will not be
rendered; if provides null, use original component instead.

Possible render types are:
+ 'prechat.header'
+ 'prechat.greeting'
+ 'prechat.content'
+ 'prechat.footer'
+ 'chat.header'
+ 'chat.greeting'
+ 'chat.content'
+ 'chat.footer'
+ 'postchat.header'
+ 'postchat.greeting'
+ 'postchat.content'
+ 'postchat.footer'
+ 'offline.header'
+ 'offline.greeting'
+ 'offline.content'
+ 'offline.footer'
+ 'login.header'
+ 'login.greeting'
+ 'login.content'
+ 'login.footer'
+ 'ban.header'
+ 'ban.content'
+ 'ban.footer'

properties.name: prechatForm
properties.description: Useful api to get/set prechat form

properties.name: postchatForm
properties.description: Useful api to get/set postchat form

properties.name: offlineForm
properties.description: Useful api to get/set offline message form

properties.name: chatContent
properties.description: Useful api to get/set chat content

properties.name: extendedWindow
properties.description: Useful api to get/set extended window

properties.name: onReady
properties.description:
API that will be triggered when live chat app is ready, which is after JavaScript has been
downloaded and initialized.

properties.name: onButtonWillDisplay
properties.description:
API that will be triggered before certain button is rendered, providing useful API to get/set
the button, also provide feature to prevent rendering if necessary. If function returns `false`,
it will prevent rendering current button.

properties.name: onInvitationWillDisplay
properties.description:
API that will be triggered before certain invitation is rendered, providing useful API to get/set
the invitation, also provide feature to prevent rendering if necessary. If function returns `false`,
it will prevent rendering current invitation.

properties.name: onWindowWillDisplay
properties.description:
API that will be triggered before chat window is rendered, providing useful API to get/set
the chat window, also provide feature to prevent rendering if necessary. If function returns `false`,
it will prevent rendering current chat window.

properties.name: site_id
properties.description: Site Id

properties.name: dynamic
properties.description: if dynamic campaign
